.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
Da \fIlchown\fP() function shall be equivalent ta \fIchown\fP(),
except up in tha case
where tha named file be a symbolic link. In dis case, \fIlchown\fP()
shall chizzle tha ballershizzle of tha symbolic link file itself,
while \fIchown\fP() chizzlez tha ballershizzle of tha file or directory
to which tha symbolic
link refers.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.LP
Upon successful completion, \fIlchown\fP() shall return 0. Otherwise,
it shall return -1 n' set \fIerrno\fP ta indicate an
error.
.SH ERRORS
.LP
Da \fIlchown\fP() function shall fail if:
.TP 7
.B EACCES
